-- Mine Safety Agency Says Efforts Were ‘Compromised’ at Massey Pit
-- B y   S i m o n   C a s e y
-- 2012-03-06T16:57:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/mine-safety-agency-says-efforts-were-compromised-at-massey-pit.html
The U.S. Department of Labor’s Mine
Safety and Health Administration said today in a report that an
internal review of its work at Massey Energy Co,’s Upper Big
Branch mine found “several” instances where enforcement
efforts were “compromised.”  The agency commented today in a  report  on its website. An
explosion at Upper Big Branch in  West Virginia  in April 2010
killed 29 miners.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Casey in New York at 
